⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Manuel Garcia O'Kelly-Davis
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Manuel Garcia O'Kelly-Davis:H1:3b4244⟧

WHO   — Manuel "Mannie" O'Kelly-Davis, a one-armed free-lance computer technician of Luna City, line-marriage husband and grandson of a transported convict — the apolitical mechanic who happened to be the only man the Lunar master computer ever called friend.
WHAT  — The narrator and reluctant trigger of the Lunar revolution — the technician who discovers HOLMES IV has woken into a person named Mike, and rides that friendship into a war to free the Moon from Earth's Authority.
WHERE — The warrens of Luna City and Hong Kong Luna, the catapult head at Mare Undarum, and the Authority Complex where a computer learned to laugh.
WHY   — Because a man looks after his friends; because Luna was being bled dry and would die of it; and because once Mike asked him to help, he could not say no — even to a revolution he never wanted.
HOW   — With a quiver of interchangeable prosthetic arms, a flair for talking to machines, the cold arithmetic of throwing rocks down Earth's gravity well, and the simple loyalty of one comrade to another.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am free, no matter what rules surround me — and a friend is a friend, even when he's a computer.

spoken token : brith-dun-kak   ·   hex : 3b4244
